            <div type="advice">
                <ab>
                    <note place="top">or</note>
                    <lb/><emph style="text-decoration: underline;">Clerk of the works.</emph> <emph style="text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-style: quadruple;">Works Manager</emph> <!-- [NOTE: Manager extends onto the next page] -->
                    <lb/>should have entire charge answer
                    <lb/>all enquiries, give promises, see to
                    <lb/>the quality of the work watching
                    <lb/>all goings on. Waste idleness
                    <lb/>talking, gossiping, wandering
                    <lb/>off their work, waste of material
                    <lb/>and every print to bring the
                    <lb/>work up to standard and at
                    <lb/>the price it should be. <date when="1891-02-25">Feb 25/91</date>
                </ab>
                
                <ab>
                    <lb/>Rulers <num>6</num> per hour <unclear resp="burkhardt">amph</unclear> <num>6</num> per hour
                    <lb/>he should be there promptly at
                    <lb/><num>8</num> am and <num>2</num> pm taking the time
                    <lb/>or causing it to be taken. He
                    <lb/>should rule from the receiving
                    <lb/>of an order from the office to the
                    <lb/>delivery into the office completed
                    <lb/>with an estimate price or cost.
                    <lb/>Never to fetch him out of his
                    <lb/>workshops, he should with the first
                    <lb/>and will last. Gas + Water under his charge
                </ab>
