            <!-- [NOTE: downwards curly brace thing] -->
            <div type="advice">
                <ab>
                    <lb/>Works
                    <lb/>Manager
                    <lb/>I am convinced more and more if a practical
                    <lb/>clever works manager being necessary, a master
                    <lb/>would be the best because he is interested in the
                    <lb/>dividend.
                </ab>
                <ab>
                    <lb/>Ruling there is no skilled weighing up of the amount
                    <lb/>done nor any planning of the jobs to get the most out
                    <lb/>of this was done day by day and each machine
                    <lb/>put out its pull however the difference would be
                    <lb/>very great, incredibly more than now.
                    <lb/>The same in binders of Stationary
                    <lb/>printing machines.
                </ab>
                <ab>
                    <!-- [NOTE: I seriously have no idea what started going on with his handwriting here it started getting reaaaaaaaaal bad] -->
                    <lb/>Contracts - directs, govern, engages, discharges, pays,
                    <lb/> and sees every job done and gives its <unclear resp="burkhardt">workmens</unclear>
                    <lb/>cost and material cost and sends an approximate
                    <lb/>value which is checked over peroperly estimated where
                    <lb/>necessary talked over by partners in <unclear resp="burkhardt">council</unclear> and agreed
                    <lb/>whom always pass the work before going down <unclear resp="burkhardt">pelllo</unclear>
                    <lb/>all prices <unclear resp="burkhardt" reason="illegible">weroid</unclear> and estimate outward, posts his own
