                <ab>
                    <lb/>Sunday's
                    <lb/><date when="1890-11-09">Nov 9th 1890</date>
                    <lb/>I would desire that
                    <lb/>my children <choice><orig>thro</orig><reg>through</reg></choice> life make a
                    <lb/>rule of attending Church at
                    <lb/>least once a day. I may say
                    <lb/>for <num>30</num> years and more I have
                    <lb/>rarely missed Morning + Evening
                    <lb/>Services + Festivals <unclear resp="burkhardt">for a Divine rote</unclear> <!-- [NOTE: This may be about a person actually. is for, father?] -->
                    <lb/>the better he spent his Sundays, the
                    <lb/>better his weeks duties prospered!!!
                    <lb/>Psalm 119 8) <emph style="text-decoration:underline;">176 verses</emph>
                    <lb/>22 chapters. Eight is the <!-- [NOTE: I think this is because 176/22 is 8, which is also the number of verses within each stanza (chapter)]-->
                    <lb/>Number of Perfection.
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="instruction">
